   capable of providing reliable opacities up to 18,00023,000 cm(-1), while
   the highest applicable wavenumber range drops as T rises. We suggest
   caution is used for T> 1000 K simulations. Comparison to recent
   experiments at 1000 K, 1550 K and 1773 K shows that the Ames-1000 K line
   list and HITEMP perform similarly in the 3200-3800 cm(-1) and 4600-5200
